# Subagent TTS — Priority is Mandatory

Every `friday-speak.py` call inside a Task subagent (explore / shell / generalPurpose) **MUST** include `FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1`. Subagents use the **young-sounding** sticky pool (Jenny, Aria, Michelle, Blue, Nancy — see `pick-session-voice.py`). Do not force Ana or other toddler timbres.

## Why this matters

Without priority, a subagent's TTS waits behind the global speak lock — which the main agent or ambient may already hold. The result is **silent subagents**: they technically "speak" but the audio is swallowed or delayed until the lock clears.

`FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY=1` pre-empts any competing TTS, kills friday-player, releases the Redis lock, and speaks immediately — exactly like a user-facing voice reply.

## Required subagent speak pattern (copy verbatim into every Task prompt)

```powershell
# Single command — no separate pick-session-voice needed (friday-speak.py auto-picks if missing)
cd d:\code\openclaw; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_SESSION='subagent'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "your message here"
```

**No separate `pick-session-voice.py` call needed.** `friday-speak.py` auto-detects missing session voice and spawns the picker in the background.

## Test command — verify subagent TTS is working

Run this to confirm a subagent voice fires with priority and is heard through the speakers:

```powershell
cd d:\code\openclaw; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_SESSION='subagent'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'; $env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'; python skill-gateway/scripts/friday-speak.py "Subagent priority TTS test. If you hear this, the fix is working."
```

Expected: a teen/young-adult voice speaks the test line immediately, pre-empting any ambient TTS.

## Enforcement checklist

When writing any Task subagent prompt, verify the prompt contains:

- [ ] `$env:FRIDAY_TTS_SESSION='subagent'`
- [ ] `$env:FRIDAY_TTS_PRIORITY='1'`
- [ ] `$env:FRIDAY_TTS_BYPASS_CURSOR_DEFER='true'`

All three on every single `friday-speak.py` invocation. Missing any one of these is a bug.
